---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="API reference" description="session-loam API surface: Store, Entry, SearchResult, RankWeights. Python library + loam-cli subcommand reference.">

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <section class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-accent-green mb-3 font-mono">// DOCS / API</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 leading-tight">API reference</h1>
      <p class="text-base text-muted leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Complete v0.1.0 surface — Python library plus the <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">loam-cli</code> subcommand set.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Store</h2>
      <pre class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code><span class="text-accent">from</span> session_loam <span class="text-accent">import</span> Store, Entry, RankWeights</code></pre>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mt-6 mb-2"><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">Store.open(agent=None, *, path=None) → Store</code></h3>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm">
        Open (or create) the store for an agent. Resolution order: explicit arg →
        <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">$LOAM_AGENT</code> →
        hostname. Path: explicit arg → <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">$LOAM_BASE_DIR/&lt;agent&gt;.db</code> →
        <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">~/.session-loam/&lt;agent&gt;.db</code>.
        WAL mode + foreign keys on. Refuses to open if on-disk schema major differs.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mt-6 mb-2"><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">store.write(entry: Entry) → Entry</code></h3>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm">
        Persist. Fills in <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">id</code>, <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">agent</code>, <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">created_at</code>, <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">last_accessed</code>.
        If <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">entry.supersedes</code> is set, the predecessor's <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">superseded_by</code> back-ref is updated in the same transaction.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mt-6 mb-2"><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">store.get(entry_id) → Entry</code></h3>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm">
        Fetch one by id. Reinforces (bumps <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">last_accessed</code> and <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">access_count</code>).
        Raises <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">EntryNotFound</code> if missing. Visible to <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">get</code> even when superseded.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mt-6 mb-2"><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">store.search(query, *, tags=None, type=None, since=None, until=None, include_superseded=False, limit=20, weights=DEFAULT_WEIGHTS, reinforce=True) → list[SearchResult]</code></h3>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm">
        FTS5 MATCH against content + tags. Tag filter is AND across the provided set.
        Time-range is inclusive on both ends. Superseded entries are hidden unless opted in.
        Ranking: bm25 + multiplicative boosts from <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">weights</code>.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mt-6 mb-2"><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">store.recent(*, type=None, tags=None, since=None, until=None, include_superseded=False, limit=20, reinforce=True) → list[Entry]</code></h3>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm">
        Time-ordered fetch (newest <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">created_at</code> first). Same filters as <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">search</code>, no text query.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-text mt-6 mb-2"><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">store.close()</code></h3>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-2 text-sm">
        Close the connection. Also exposed via context manager: <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">with Store.open() as store: …</code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Entry</h2>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3 text-sm">Dataclass.</p>
      <pre class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>@dataclass
class Entry:
    type: str
    content: str
    id: str | None              = None
    agent: str | None           = None
    source: str | None          = None
    confidence: float | None    = None
    tags: list[str]             = []
    created_at: str | None      = None
    last_accessed: str | None   = None
    access_count: int           = 0
    supersedes: str | None      = None
    superseded_by: str | None   = None
    attestations: list[dict]    = []
    metadata: dict              = {}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">SearchResult</h2>
      <pre class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>@dataclass
class SearchResult:
    entry: Entry
    rank: float       <span class="text-muted"># bm25 + boosts, higher = better</span>
    snippet: str      <span class="text-muted"># FTS5 snippet, [matched] terms bracketed</span></code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">RankWeights</h2>
      <pre class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>@dataclass(frozen=True)
class RankWeights:
    recency_half_life_days: float = <span class="text-warm">14.0</span>
    recency_strength:       float = <span class="text-warm">0.5</span>
    confidence_strength:    float = <span class="text-warm">0.3</span>
    access_count_strength:  float = <span class="text-warm">0.1</span></code></pre>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3 text-sm">
        Set any <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">*_strength</code> to <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">0.0</code> to disable that signal.
        Pass a custom instance to <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">store.search(..., weights=...)</code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Exceptions</h2>
      <ul class="text-muted space-y-2 max-w-2xl ml-4">
        <li><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">EntryNotFound</code> — raised by <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">store.get()</code> when no entry matches the id.</li>
        <li><code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">SchemaVersionMismatch</code> — raised by <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">Store.open()</code> when the on-disk schema major differs from the library's.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">Helpers</h2>
      <pre class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code><span class="text-accent">from</span> session_loam.search <span class="text-accent">import</span> escape_query

<span class="text-muted"># Wrap a literal string as an FTS5 phrase, escaping double quotes</span>
phrase = escape_query(<span class="text-warm">'he said "hi"'</span>)
<span class="text-muted"># -> '"he said ""hi"""'</span>
store.search(query=phrase)</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-accent">loam-cli</h2>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3 text-sm">
        Subprocess interface mirroring the Python surface. Single-line JSON on stdout by default; pass <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">--pretty</code> for indentation. All commands accept <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">--agent</code> and <code class="bg-code-bg border border-code-border px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">--path</code> overrides.
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="text-sm w-full">
          <thead>
            <tr class="text-left text-muted border-b border-border">
              <th class="py-2 pr-4">Command</th>
              <th class="py-2">Purpose</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-muted">
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli write</code></td><td class="py-2">Add an entry. <code class="text-xs">--content</code> reads stdin when omitted or set to <code class="text-xs">-</code>.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli get &lt;id&gt;</code></td><td class="py-2">Fetch one entry. <code class="text-xs">--no-reinforce</code> skips the access-count bump.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli search</code></td><td class="py-2">FTS5 + filters + ranking. Emits JSON array of <code class="text-xs">&#123;entry, rank, snippet&#125;</code>.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli recent</code></td><td class="py-2">Time-ordered fetch with filters. Emits JSON array of entries.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli ls</code></td><td class="py-2">Per-agent summary: count, by_type, top tags, last accessed. <code class="text-xs">--json</code> for machine output.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli supersede</code></td><td class="py-2">Write a replacement; inherits unspecified fields from predecessor.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli prune</code></td><td class="py-2">Filter-driven cleanup. Dry-run by default; <code class="text-xs">--apply</code> to commit.</td></tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border/40"><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli export</code></td><td class="py-2">Dump every entry as JSONL on stdout (ordered, no reinforce).</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4"><code class="text-xs">loam-cli import</code></td><td class="py-2">Restore from JSONL on stdin or <code class="text-xs">--file</code>. <code class="text-xs">--replace</code> overwrites by id.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</Base>
